## Tail (rough one-liners, no structure)

Quick captures that don't deserve a full section yet — `/discover` will read these too and might combine them with the above to produce stronger candidates.

- *e.g., "Something for small podcast networks to coordinate cross-promotion."*
- *e.g., "A tool that automatically detects when your shipped React app's bundle size regresses and tells you which import did it."*
- *e.g., "Better expense splitting for shared houses where one roommate buys everything and the rest pay back inconsistently."*
- ...

---

## What to avoid

If there are categories or product types you'd specifically NOT want `/discover` to surface (regardless of how trendy or technically interesting), note them here. This is the inverse signal — what to NOT brainstorm.

- *e.g., "Anything in crypto / Web3 — not a domain I want to operate in."*
- *e.g., "B2B SaaS targeting enterprise sales cycles — wrong scale for me as a solo builder."*
- *e.g., "Consumer mobile games — not my taste."*
- ...

